# Codex Local Notes — WorldView / ODIN OSINT

## Canonical Docs

Use these as source of truth, in this order:

1. AGENTS.md — agent operating rules, commands, hardware constraints
2. TASKS.md — task registry and canonical tech stack
3. architecture.md — system architecture
4. decisions.md — architecture decisions
5. CLAUDE.md — broader project context and historical notes

Do not duplicate large sections from those files here.

## Current Engineering Posture

WorldView is moving from "many map layers" toward a fusion system:

Raw source -> SourceRef -> Observation -> WorldObject / IncidentCandidate -> FusionLink -> ReviewItem -> approved graph/timeline/globe surface.

The next strategic milestone is TASK-108 Fusion Core:
- canonical observations
- stable world_object_id / entity identity
- spatiotemporal fusion
- source lineage
- analyst review queue
- later: vision as another Observation producer

Vision / YOLO is not the foundation. It should plug into Fusion Core later.

## Repo Hygiene

Before changing files:
- check branch and dirty state
- do not touch unrelated untracked files
- use worktrees for large feature branches
- keep commits scoped and intentional

Do not auto-delete branches, worktrees, or untracked files unless explicitly asked.

## Verification

Run commands from service directories:

Backend:
cd services/backend && uv run pytest && uv run ruff check app/ && uv run mypy app/

Frontend:
cd services/frontend && npm run lint && npm run type-check && npm test

Intelligence:
cd services/intelligence && uv run pytest

Data ingestion:
cd services/data-ingestion && uv run pytest

## Architecture Guardrails

- Neo4j writes use deterministic Cypher templates only.
- Neo4j reads may use LLM-generated Cypher if read-only guarded.
- All Neo4j queries use parameter binding.
- Backend code is async-first.
- Frontend TypeScript uses no `any`.
- Cesium bulk rendering uses primitives / collections, not Entity API.
- No API keys in code.
- GDELT ingestion uses raw files pipeline, not old DOC API collector.

## Hardware Constraint

Single RTX 5090, 32 GB VRAM.
Only one LLM runtime at a time.
Use `odin.sh swap` for mode changes.
Do not run multiple vLLM / llama.cpp containers concurrently.

## Style Preference

Prefer decisive, small, reviewable steps.
For specs and plans, be explicit enough that another agent can implement without guessing.
For code, follow existing local patterns before introducing abstractions.
